
    Ted Baker boss takes leave of absence

        

    
        
                
                
            
        Fashion chain Ted Baker's chief executive Ray Kelvin is to take a voluntary leave of absence amid allegations of harassment.Last week, an online petition launched by employees accused 62-year-old Mr Kelvin of inappropriate comments and behaviour, including "forced hugging".Ted Baker said it had appointed a law firm to conduct an independent external investigation into the allegations.Chief operating officer Lindsay Page has been named acting chief executive.
            

